TITLE: Azure Service Bus Queue Configuration in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides a configuration example for an Azure Service Bus receive endpoint using MassTransit. It sets up properties like PrefetchCount, ConcurrentMessageLimit, LockDuration, and MaxAutoRenewDuration. The code requires MassTransit and a valid connection string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/masstransit/masstransit/blob/develop/doc/content/3.documentation/2.configuration/2.transports/3.azure-service-bus.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
services.AddMassTransit(x =>
{
    x.UsingAzureServiceBus((context, cfg) =>
    {
        cfg.Host("connection-string");

        cfg.ReceiveEndpoint("input-queue", e =>
        {
            // all of these are optional!!

            e.PrefetchCount = 100;

            // number of messages to deliver concurrently
            e.ConcurrentMessageLimit = 100;

            // default, but shown for example
            e.LockDuration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5);

            // lock will be renewed up to 30 minutes
            e.MaxAutoRenewDuration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30);
        });
    });
});

```

