TITLE: Redelivering Messages on Missing Saga Instance in C# with MassTransit
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a saga state machine that redelivers a message if a matching saga state machine instance is not found. The redelivery configuration allows for five attempts at intervals of one second before producing a fault if unsuccessful. It showcases the handling of events and correlation of message IDs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/masstransit/masstransit/blob/develop/doc/content/3.documentation/2.configuration/1.sagas/2.event.md#2025-04-18_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public record OrderAddressValidated(Guid OrderId);

public class OrderStateMachine :
    MassTransitStateMachine<OrderState>
{
    public OrderStateMachine()
    {
        Event(() => OrderAddressValidated, e =>
        {
            e.CorrelateById(context => context.Message.OrderId);

            e.OnMissingInstance(m => m.Redeliver(r =>
            {
                r.Interval(5, 1000);
                r.OnRedeliveryLimitReached(n => n.Fault());
            }));
        });
    }

    public Event<OrderAddressValidated> OrderAddressValidated { get; private set; }
}
```

